pageContext.claim: “Kelly O'Donnell, you know, she's a fading reporter for NBC. Do you know that? She was on -- she said, well, you know, they have a crowd tonight. Behind her, it looked like 25,000 people. That's what we have, by the way, a lot more coming in. She said he's got maybe a thousand people. A thousand?!”
pageContext.analysis: Trump drew a large crowd to his rally in Nevada during the coronavirus pandemic, but the outdoor venue where he held the event was not packed, as NBC reporter Kelly O'Donnell noted during an on-air segment. She later tweeted images of the crowd.
